WEBVTT

00:07.678 --> 00:10.741
♪ Love
It wants to heal you ♪

00:10.741 --> 00:12.143
♪ Love ♪

00:12.143 --> 00:15.015
♪ And see the real you ♪

00:15.015 --> 00:18.319
♪ But you have to open up ♪

00:18.319 --> 00:23.224
- ♪ When you need
a little love ♪
- ♪ Na, na, na, na, na, na ♪

00:23.224 --> 00:26.357
- ♪ Yeah, yeah ♪
- ♪ Na, na, na, na, na, na ♪

00:26.357 --> 00:29.630
- ♪ Yeah ♪
- ♪ Na, na, na, na, na, na ♪

00:31.031 --> 00:33.634
♪ We need a little ♪

00:33.634 --> 00:37.508
♪ Love ♪♪

00:38.409 --> 00:39.670
Wow, Sheryl,
that was awesome.

00:39.670 --> 00:41.642
Aw, thank a lot,
you're so sweet.

00:43.614 --> 00:45.416
And how was I?

00:45.416 --> 00:47.378
I mean, I didn't think
I'd have to beg for it.

00:47.378 --> 00:50.181
- You were great.
- Oh, stop.
You're embarrassing me.

00:51.552 --> 00:54.655
Thanks, Hannah. Thanks, Sheryl.
That was just beautiful.

00:54.655 --> 00:57.088
- [bellows] Lunch!
- [bell rings]

00:57.088 --> 01:00.091
Sorry about Ronnie. He gets
excited on Fajita Fridays.

01:00.091 --> 01:03.464
It's not just fajitas. This
morning, I was in wardrobe,
when he heard there was an

01:03.464 --> 01:04.565
[screams] omelet bar.

01:04.565 --> 01:05.736
[Hannah groans]

01:05.736 --> 01:07.468
[cell phone rings]

01:08.399 --> 01:10.070
Hey, Lilly.
Is Oliver there yet?

01:10.070 --> 01:12.573
No, and he should've
been here an hour ago!

01:12.573 --> 01:16.547
- Stop bugging me about it!
- I get it, you're nervous.

01:16.547 --> 01:18.509
You haven't seen
Oliver in two months

01:18.509 --> 01:20.681
and you're scared he's gonna
walk in, take one look at you

01:20.681 --> 01:23.714
and go "Ugh, she is not
as pretty as I remembered."

01:23.714 --> 01:28.319
[sobbing] No... I just
couldn't find the tweezers.

01:30.791 --> 01:34.495
Ooh, ah, bathroom cabinet,
third drawer down.

01:34.495 --> 01:37.768
- Don't worry, you look great.
- You can't even see me!

01:38.629 --> 01:39.770
Jeesh!

01:39.770 --> 01:42.773
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh, whoa ♪

01:44.835 --> 01:47.438
Ow! Ow!

01:48.439 --> 01:49.640
Ow!

01:50.811 --> 01:51.842
Are they even?

01:51.842 --> 01:55.115
- Sure, they look great.
- Liar!

01:57.488 --> 02:02.523
"Come on, Dad, let Lilly
move in! It'll be so much fun."

02:03.794 --> 02:05.726
OK, all right.
I know, I know.

02:05.726 --> 02:08.699
I'm acting stupid, I'm sorry.
It's gonna stop right now.

02:08.699 --> 02:11.732
- [doorbell rings]
- He's here! Get out of the way!

02:11.732 --> 02:16.537
- [thudding]
- Well, that got my morning
bran muffin moving south.

02:19.770 --> 02:22.713
- [gasps] Ollie-pop!
- Lilly-pop!

02:22.713 --> 02:25.646
Hi! Oh, wow,
look at this place.

02:25.646 --> 02:27.318
- Yeah.
- Hey, Mr. Stewart.
How you doing?

02:27.318 --> 02:30.221
Stop it, son,
we both know you don't care.

02:30.221 --> 02:33.224
He so gets me.
[clears throat]

02:33.224 --> 02:35.426
- I missed you.
- I missed you more!

02:35.426 --> 02:36.927
It's gonna be so fun.

02:36.927 --> 02:40.491
I did all my homework, I took
off work, it's gonna be perfect!

02:40.491 --> 02:44.565
- Well, almost perfect.
- Oh... Oh, no.

02:44.565 --> 02:46.697
Oh, it's my eyebrows.
They're uneven.

02:46.697 --> 02:50.801
- Look away!
- Lilly, it's not your eyebrows.

02:50.801 --> 02:52.643
- Oh...
- It's Miley.

02:52.643 --> 02:54.245
Miley's eyebrows
look great.

02:54.245 --> 02:57.408
It's that one funny tooth
I'm begging her to fix.

02:57.408 --> 02:59.780
I'm not talking about her teeth,
I'm talking about Jake.

02:59.780 --> 03:01.652
Why are we talking
about Jake's teeth?

03:01.652 --> 03:04.255
Because they were nibbling
all over another girl's
ear last night.

03:04.255 --> 03:05.416
He was cheating?

03:05.416 --> 03:07.958
Yesterday, my band
was in Phoenix where Jake's

03:07.958 --> 03:11.862
shooting his movie, and
my drummer texted me this.

03:14.725 --> 03:18.329
- Oh, my...
- Lee! Oh, Miley!

03:19.600 --> 03:21.802
- Oliver! So good to see you!
- Hi.

03:21.802 --> 03:25.306
Look at us back together.
This is going to be
the best weekend ever!

03:25.306 --> 03:28.379
[Lilly and Oliver] Yeah...

03:28.879 --> 03:30.281
[Miley] Whoo!

03:30.281 --> 03:31.812
Here we go, everybody!

03:33.714 --> 03:34.985
♪ Come on ♪

03:34.985 --> 03:37.948
♪ You get the limo
out front ♪

03:37.948 --> 03:39.520
♪ Oooh ♪

03:39.520 --> 03:42.693
♪ Hottest styles
Every shoe, every color ♪

03:42.693 --> 03:46.727
♪ Yeah, when you're famous
it can be kind of fun ♪

03:46.727 --> 03:50.731
♪ It's really you
but no one ever discovers ♪

03:50.731 --> 03:54.835
♪ Who would have thought
that a girl like me ♪

03:54.835 --> 03:59.410
♪ Would double
as a superstar ♪

03:59.410 --> 04:00.741
Whooo!

04:00.741 --> 04:04.775
♪ You get the best
of both worlds ♪

04:04.775 --> 04:06.747
♪ Chill it out
Take it slow ♪

04:06.747 --> 04:08.619
♪ Then you rock out the show ♪

04:08.619 --> 04:12.623
♪ You get the best
of both worlds ♪

04:12.623 --> 04:15.326
♪ Mix it all together
and you know ♪

04:15.326 --> 04:18.488
♪ That it's the best
of both worlds ♪♪

04:21.762 --> 04:24.295
♪ Ooh, ah, oh, oh, oh ♪♪

04:24.295 --> 04:28.268
[Lilly and Oliver] Yeah...

04:28.268 --> 04:31.602
OK... We just passed nice
and headed straight
into awkward.

04:32.773 --> 04:35.306
I get it. You feel bad
because you're a couple

04:35.306 --> 04:36.947
and without Jake
I'm Little Miss Lonely.

04:36.947 --> 04:40.311
[Lilly and Oliver] Yeah...

04:40.311 --> 04:43.554
OK, we just passed awkward and
headed straight into creepy.

04:45.285 --> 04:46.517
[cell phone rings]

04:46.517 --> 04:48.859
Hello? Oh, hey, Andy.

04:48.859 --> 04:52.823
Andy Samberg, absolutely adores
me, doing my holiday special.

04:52.823 --> 04:55.295
What do you mean you can't
do my holiday special?

04:57.898 --> 05:00.931
- I never trusted Jake. Never!
- I know, I know.

05:00.931 --> 05:03.934
Miserable two-timing
big blond bag of butthead!

05:03.934 --> 05:07.538
- I know, I know.
- Men. Worthless. All of them!

05:07.538 --> 05:09.540
I know! I...

05:09.540 --> 05:11.342
I see,
I don't know about that.

05:11.342 --> 05:15.346
Oh, honey, you're not a man.
You're Oliver.

05:17.448 --> 05:19.520
Well, all right.

05:19.520 --> 05:22.753
Look, when she gets off
the phone, you have to
tell her really quick.

05:22.753 --> 05:23.794
Like you're ripping
off a bandage.

05:23.794 --> 05:25.556
Oh, no, no, no.
I can never do that.

05:25.556 --> 05:28.959
I usually like to soak it in
hot water and let it fall off...

05:28.959 --> 05:32.663
This could be a very
lonely weekend for you.

05:32.663 --> 05:34.765
- I'm gonna go tell her.
- OK...

05:36.367 --> 05:38.739
Unbelievable!
People make commitments

05:38.739 --> 05:41.472
and then they let you down.
It's like you can't
trust anybody!

05:41.472 --> 05:44.545
Well... [clears throat]

05:44.545 --> 05:48.619
- Funny you should say that.
- Oh!

05:48.619 --> 05:52.653
It's almost time for my holiday
special, and now one of my guest
stars has flaked out.

05:53.884 --> 05:57.428
Huh! Well, speaking
of flakey actors...

05:57.428 --> 05:59.990
This is crazy.

05:59.990 --> 06:03.133
It's totally getting me
all freaked out and now it's
gonna ruin my performance.

06:03.133 --> 06:04.935
I cannot
let that happen.

06:04.935 --> 06:07.768
The kids of America,
a good part of Europe,

06:07.768 --> 06:12.473
most of Asia, and South America
and Australia deserve better
than that!

06:12.473 --> 06:15.375
But I just gotta
focus on the positive:

06:15.375 --> 06:17.878
I mean, I've got great friends
and a wonderful boyfriend.

06:17.878 --> 06:20.150
Oliver's got
something to tell you.

06:20.150 --> 06:22.382
Yeah... [chuckles]

06:22.382 --> 06:24.054
You left out Canada.

06:25.416 --> 06:27.057
I didn't wanna
come off braggy, but...

06:28.419 --> 06:31.161
You know what? It's OK.
I can find another guest star.

06:31.161 --> 06:32.893
I've got tons of
celebrities in my phone.

06:32.893 --> 06:35.896
Ooh, hate him.
She hates me.

06:35.896 --> 06:38.429
Does not look good in HD!

06:40.531 --> 06:42.573
You are such
a bandage soaker!

06:42.573 --> 06:44.935
Hey, you saw
how upset she got!

06:44.935 --> 06:47.508
If I tell her now it'll
ruin her holiday special.

06:47.508 --> 06:51.612
Yeah, and if you don't tell
and she finds out that
we knew he was cheating,

06:51.612 --> 06:53.544
she's gonna hate me!

06:53.544 --> 06:56.447
I mean, we're best friends,
we don't keep secrets
from each other.

06:56.447 --> 06:59.620
OK, so you want her
to have a broken heart

06:59.620 --> 07:01.552
and a rotten
holiday special?

07:01.552 --> 07:05.055
What kind of
best friend are you?

07:05.055 --> 07:07.558
Oh, I hate
when you're right.

07:08.599 --> 07:10.631
So we're not gonna
kiss now, are we?

07:10.631 --> 07:13.063
Ooh... Well,
look who's right again.

07:16.166 --> 07:20.040
[sighing theatrically]
Siena...

07:23.844 --> 07:27.948
[sighing theatrically]
Siena!

07:32.683 --> 07:36.887
[sighing theatrically]
Siena!

07:36.887 --> 07:38.929
Oh, sweet Pete, son!

07:38.929 --> 07:40.931
Between the Internet
and interrupting kids,

07:40.931 --> 07:43.494
it's no wonder
newspapers are dyin' out!

07:43.494 --> 07:44.865
You know there's gonna
be a world full of

07:44.865 --> 07:47.237
puppies and parakeets
with nothin' to pee on,

07:47.237 --> 07:49.840
and it's gonna be
on your head!

07:49.840 --> 07:51.471
Pun intended.

07:51.471 --> 07:54.104
I'm sorry, it's just that
Siena's been modeling all week

07:54.104 --> 07:59.079
- and I miss her like crazy.
- For goodness sakes.

07:59.079 --> 08:03.153
Get off my lap and go
and see the girl.
You're crushin' Marmaduke!

08:03.153 --> 08:05.956
Great idea! You wanna
give me the 2,000 in cash

08:05.956 --> 08:07.518
or write me a check?

08:07.518 --> 08:10.260
What do you need two grand for?

08:10.260 --> 08:13.994
She's modeling in Peru.
Didn't I say that?

08:13.994 --> 08:17.898
I'm not giving you $2,000
to fly to Peru!

08:17.898 --> 08:22.232
If you're that dagonne lonely,
why don't you take that shirt
out for dinner and a movie.

08:24.735 --> 08:28.078
[high-pitched voice]
You're a mean man.

08:28.078 --> 08:30.781
Stop that.
That's weird.

08:40.120 --> 08:43.193
Yeah, I get it, your
girlfriend's not in Peru!

08:43.193 --> 08:44.655
You don't have to
rub it in my face!

08:47.558 --> 08:49.960
Come on, Al. If you
won't sell me the arcade,

08:49.960 --> 08:51.832
at least sell me
the pizza place.

08:51.832 --> 08:54.264
- Would that make you happy?
- Yes.

08:54.264 --> 08:55.305
Then, no!

08:57.007 --> 08:59.539
It's not just that I don't
like you, which I don't.

08:59.539 --> 09:02.242
It's that I prefer to do my
deals with people who keep

09:02.242 --> 09:05.676
their baby teeth in a Lucite
box and not their mouth!

09:05.676 --> 09:07.918
[scoffs]
I do not!

09:07.918 --> 09:11.021
OK, only one and
it's wiggling. See?

09:12.122 --> 09:14.885
Look, you're a nice...
Look, you're a kid.

09:14.885 --> 09:19.029
Get your daddy here and maybe
the two of us can talk business.

09:19.960 --> 09:21.892
Fine. Fine! You want my dad?

09:21.892 --> 09:22.963
I'll get you my dad.

09:24.665 --> 09:28.568
Mami, when does Papi get back
from the national tour
of The King and I?

09:28.568 --> 09:30.070
That long?

09:30.070 --> 09:34.244
Curse his mid-life crisis and
that beautiful baritone voice!

09:34.244 --> 09:36.977
[speaks Spanish]

09:36.977 --> 09:38.909
Four years of Spanish
and that's the best you can do?

09:38.909 --> 09:41.081
Five. And yes!

09:42.713 --> 09:44.955
The point is, for $2,000
I'll pretend to be your dad.

09:44.955 --> 09:47.688
Ha! Like anyone would
believe you're my dad.

09:47.688 --> 09:50.190
Hey, if it doesn't work, I'll
set you up with one of Siena's

09:50.190 --> 09:52.592
b-b-b-bikini model friends.

09:52.592 --> 09:54.364
Papi!

09:56.596 --> 10:00.731
♪ Yeah, yeah, hey, yeah
Wha-oo ♪♪

10:00.731 --> 10:03.373
[Lilly] No, Oliver, I
haven't said anything to her.

10:03.373 --> 10:06.777
I said I wouldn't and
I won't, now stop nagging.

10:06.777 --> 10:08.909
- [flushing]
 - What was that?

10:08.909 --> 10:12.282
Was that a flush?
Oh, have a little class!

10:12.282 --> 10:14.845
I'll talk to you later.
Goodbye.

10:14.845 --> 10:15.946
[phone beeps]

10:19.790 --> 10:20.921
[loud whisper] Miley!

10:22.653 --> 10:24.624
Are you sleeping?

10:28.398 --> 10:30.801
OK, look...

10:30.801 --> 10:33.003
I promised Oliver I wouldn't
say anything to you.

10:33.003 --> 10:36.636
So I won't, OK?
I'll just talk to myself.

10:36.636 --> 10:39.639
Gee, Lilly, Jake is
such a terrible boyfriend.

10:39.639 --> 10:42.242
If he loved Miley
he would be here right now.

10:42.242 --> 10:44.644
Yep, she should
break up with him.

10:44.644 --> 10:47.718
Break up with him.
Break up with him...

10:51.682 --> 10:55.125
- Lilly? Wake up.
- Hmm? Is everything OK?

10:56.326 --> 10:58.328
I was having
the strangest dream.

10:58.328 --> 11:00.731
I was mad at Jake
'cause he wasn't here.

11:00.731 --> 11:03.233
Huh. Yeah.
Yeah, he isn't here.

11:03.233 --> 11:05.365
He's hardly ever here.

11:05.365 --> 11:07.037
Huh...

11:07.037 --> 11:09.770
And in the dream I want
to tell him how I felt.

11:09.770 --> 11:11.802
How you felt, well.

11:11.802 --> 11:13.103
You should do
that right now.

11:13.103 --> 11:14.244
You should tell
him how you feel.

11:14.244 --> 11:15.275
I don't know...

11:15.275 --> 11:17.447
No, do it! Do it, do it,
do it, do it..

11:17.447 --> 11:19.049
You know what?
I think I will.

11:19.810 --> 11:24.014
- OK.
- Jake, listen.

11:24.014 --> 11:26.817
You're never around and
I'm not gonna take it anymore.

11:26.817 --> 11:28.088
Yeah! She ain't gonna take it!

11:28.088 --> 11:30.420
I know you're shooting a
movie, but Oliver's on tour

11:30.420 --> 11:32.222
- and he came back
to visit Lilly!
- Yes, he did.

11:32.222 --> 11:35.465
And, um, I guess what I'm
just trying to say is...

11:35.465 --> 11:37.327
Yeah! You can do it!
Come on, tell him!

11:37.327 --> 11:38.869
Please come home
for the weekend.

11:38.869 --> 11:41.431
- I really miss you.
- Yes! You what?

11:41.431 --> 11:43.473
You can even do
my Christmas special!

11:43.473 --> 11:45.005
It'll be so much fun.

11:45.005 --> 11:46.977
- You will?
- He will?

11:46.977 --> 11:48.739
- He will!
- Of course he will.

11:48.739 --> 11:50.741
Jake is the
best boyfriend ever!

11:50.741 --> 11:53.143
I never would've called him
if I didn't have that dream.

11:53.143 --> 11:55.015
Great.

11:58.949 --> 12:01.391
♪ Hey, yeah, hey, yeah ♪♪

12:01.391 --> 12:04.124
I still can't believe
Jake rearranged

12:04.124 --> 12:06.426
his entire shooting schedule
just to come visit me.

12:06.426 --> 12:09.199
Yeah, I can't believe
a lot of things Jake does.

12:10.360 --> 12:13.103
Dad, focus.
I need your full attention.

12:13.103 --> 12:16.306
This is very important.
Scarf or no scarf?

12:17.137 --> 12:18.308
I'm liking the scarf.

12:18.308 --> 12:19.810
- Really?
- Really.

12:19.810 --> 12:21.241
That settles it.
No scarf.

12:22.272 --> 12:24.374
Mile, the show's
not until tonight.

12:24.374 --> 12:26.416
- What's all the fuss about?
- Jake's gonna be here
any minute.

12:26.416 --> 12:28.148
What's all the fuss about?

12:28.148 --> 12:30.480
Look, I get it.
None of you guys

12:30.480 --> 12:33.423
- are exactly wild about Jake.
- Wild about him?

12:33.423 --> 12:34.955
- I can't stand the...
- [doorbell rings]

12:34.955 --> 12:36.356
He's here!

12:37.157 --> 12:39.289
[grunting]

12:39.890 --> 12:41.261
That settles it!

12:41.261 --> 12:43.964
Next Christmas, I'm asking
Santa for steel undies.

12:43.964 --> 12:47.067
- Miley!
- Jakey!

12:47.067 --> 12:49.539
- Jerky...
- I heard that.

12:51.201 --> 12:52.973
I cannot believe
you came!

12:52.973 --> 12:55.375
Hey, you needed me
and I'm here.

12:55.375 --> 12:59.009
- Hey, Mr. Stewart.
- Hey, Jake.

12:59.009 --> 13:00.510
- [knuckles cracking]
- Aah...

13:00.510 --> 13:02.552
- Daddy!
- What?

13:02.552 --> 13:04.354
That's my happy shake.

13:04.354 --> 13:06.386
Which means there's
an angry shake.

13:06.386 --> 13:08.218
You don't wanna
take that ride.

13:08.218 --> 13:11.361
- [squeaking] No, sir.
- That's my boy.

13:13.093 --> 13:15.025
They're not
numb this time.

13:15.025 --> 13:18.128
I think he's
warming up to me.

13:18.128 --> 13:21.231
- Hey, Lilly.
- Jake, hi...

13:21.231 --> 13:24.304
Look at you.
You just look so good.

13:24.304 --> 13:26.106
- Little hard there!
- Oh, I'm sorry.

13:26.106 --> 13:28.478
I'm overcome with emotions.
And feelings.

13:28.478 --> 13:31.081
- Very strong feelings.
- Release!

13:32.542 --> 13:36.286
♪ Yo, Mike Stanley's back
With a slide and a shake ♪

13:36.286 --> 13:38.989
♪ He's ready to roll
and that's no mis... ♪ Jake!

13:40.390 --> 13:43.924
Jake's here. [chuckles]
Why is Jake here?

13:43.924 --> 13:45.956
Just supporting
my girl.

13:45.956 --> 13:48.198
You're not the only good
boyfriend on the planet.

13:48.198 --> 13:51.431
[chuckles nervously]
Jake's here.

13:51.431 --> 13:54.364
Is stupid part of the
whole Mike Stanley thing?

13:57.307 --> 13:59.039
No...

13:59.039 --> 14:02.042
Well, Jake and I have got to go.
We've got rehearsals.

14:02.042 --> 14:03.473
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
You guys go on.

14:03.473 --> 14:07.147
We'll meet up with you.
We need some alone time

14:07.147 --> 14:09.079
- Oh, yeah!
- Know what I'm sayin'?

14:09.079 --> 14:12.923
- I know. All right.
- You kids get out of here.

14:12.923 --> 14:14.955
Crazy...
What did you do?

14:20.090 --> 14:22.532
- So, where's your dad?
- He'll be here.

14:22.532 --> 14:25.035
He just likes to
make an entrance.

14:25.035 --> 14:28.468
[up-tempo disco plays]

14:36.246 --> 14:37.507
[rolling R's]
Rico!

14:37.507 --> 14:40.010
Uh... Papi...!

14:40.951 --> 14:43.954
You must be Al Blaine.

14:43.954 --> 14:47.257
I am Rico Senior.

14:47.257 --> 14:51.391
May I call you Al?
Of course I can, I just did.

14:51.391 --> 14:55.395
Watch, I'll do it again.
Al.

14:57.897 --> 15:03.273
Such a lovely name.
And you are a lovely man.

15:03.273 --> 15:04.604
You wanna do business
or you wanna

15:04.604 --> 15:06.176
take me out
for a malted?

15:06.176 --> 15:09.139
So direct. I love it.

15:09.139 --> 15:12.312
Look. I've got a
goosebump right here.

15:12.312 --> 15:15.185
Go ahead and feel.
You know you want to.

15:16.686 --> 15:19.649
I don't think he wants
to feel your goosebump, Papi.

15:19.649 --> 15:23.353
You don't want to feel
my goosebump?

15:23.353 --> 15:27.497
Oddly enough, no.
Come on, let's talk some turkey.

15:29.199 --> 15:32.963
So forceful. I'm getting
another... I won't say it.

15:32.963 --> 15:34.364
But you know.

15:34.364 --> 15:36.536
Here's what I do know.

15:36.536 --> 15:40.940
That is the worst fake accent
and goatee I've ever seen.

15:40.940 --> 15:42.342
Look, Al,
I can explain...

15:42.342 --> 15:45.345
You. You lie to me,
you disrespect me,

15:45.345 --> 15:49.149
you treat me like a fool
just to close a lousy,
stinkin' deal.

15:49.149 --> 15:51.381
I love that.

15:52.422 --> 15:54.524
Does it give you a goosebump?

15:54.524 --> 15:55.725
He knows!

15:58.188 --> 16:01.091
You want the place
that bad, you got it.

16:01.091 --> 16:03.333
My people'll send ya
the papers.

16:03.333 --> 16:05.495
And I'll take this
for my trouble.

16:05.495 --> 16:07.237
Aah... Hmm...

16:07.237 --> 16:12.572
Soft, nice. Like having a
little kitty cat on my head.

16:17.277 --> 16:20.580
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!
Siena, here I come!

16:21.751 --> 16:24.254
♪ Hey, yeah, hey, yeah ♪♪

16:24.254 --> 16:29.319
♪ When the darkness
leaves you lonely ♪

16:29.319 --> 16:33.993
♪ Or the world tries
to push you away ♪

16:37.267 --> 16:41.571
♪ When your sky
is looking troubled ♪

16:41.571 --> 16:43.703
♪ You can count on me ♪

16:43.703 --> 16:48.038
- ♪ 'Cause I'm gonna stay ♪
- ♪ I'm gonna stay ♪

16:48.038 --> 16:51.181
♪ Put your worries
in my pocket ♪

16:51.181 --> 16:54.584
♪ I've got a key
so we can lock it ♪

16:54.584 --> 17:00.190
♪ I swear that
I won't let them escape ♪

17:00.190 --> 17:04.654
All the kids for the Mrs. Santa
Claus sketch wait right here.

17:07.327 --> 17:09.559
[sighs] Look, I don't care.
We have to tell her.

17:09.559 --> 17:11.330
We can't tell her now.

17:11.330 --> 17:14.233
We have to! If she kisses
Jake and then finds out

17:14.233 --> 17:15.565
we knew he was cheating,

17:15.565 --> 17:18.637
I'm gonna end up living in a
one room apartment with my dad!

17:18.637 --> 17:21.641
Try sharing a bathroom with
a guy who's lactose intolerant

17:21.641 --> 17:24.644
and then can't say no to ice
cream. OK, it's not pleasant.

17:24.644 --> 17:26.175
♪ Understands ♪

17:26.175 --> 17:29.219
♪ Love, it wants to heal you ♪

17:29.219 --> 17:33.253
- ♪ Love ♪
- ♪ And see the real you ♪

17:33.253 --> 17:36.486
♪ But you have to open up ♪

17:36.486 --> 17:41.391
- ♪ When you need
a little love ♪
- ♪ Na, na, na, na, na, na ♪

17:41.391 --> 17:44.534
- ♪ Yeah, yeah ♪
- ♪ Na, na, na, na, na, na ♪

17:44.534 --> 17:47.737
- ♪ Yeah ♪
 - ♪ Na, na, na, na, na, na ♪

17:49.569 --> 17:55.275
♪ Need a little love ♪♪

17:56.106 --> 17:57.777
And we're... Out!

17:57.777 --> 17:59.409
[bell rings]

18:00.610 --> 18:03.113
- That was awesome, Sheryl.
- Thanks.

18:04.554 --> 18:07.187
And, again. Is there something
you want to tell me?

18:07.187 --> 18:11.461
I'm out of hot water in my
dressing room. Maybe you could
get somebody on that?

18:11.461 --> 18:14.664
Oh, and you were great.
But I mean it about
the hot water.

18:14.664 --> 18:17.167
I'm low maintenance,
but seriously.

18:19.699 --> 18:21.501
So what'd
you guys think?

18:21.501 --> 18:24.134
Oh, it was great,
it was fantastic.
We loved the sketch.

18:24.134 --> 18:27.607
- It was a song.
- That told a story
like a sketch.

18:27.607 --> 18:29.239
In a melodic way.

18:30.380 --> 18:32.812
Yeah. You're great at
everything you do.

18:32.812 --> 18:35.815
And nobody can
take that away from you.

18:35.815 --> 18:39.249
- You just hold on to that.
- Are you guys OK?

18:39.249 --> 18:41.120
Yeah, everything's great.
Wonderful.

18:42.192 --> 18:44.624
Who's Jake?
And why is he a cheater?

18:46.556 --> 18:49.159
- Uh...
- I have no idea what
he's talking about.

18:49.159 --> 18:50.900
You said Jake
was a cheater.

18:50.900 --> 18:53.433
Did he cheat on a test?

18:54.404 --> 18:57.507
- Oliver?
- How cute is this guy?

18:57.507 --> 19:00.370
- Why don't you run along?
- What's going on?

19:02.912 --> 19:04.814
Jake cheated on you.

19:04.814 --> 19:06.676
What?

19:06.676 --> 19:08.748
My drummer sent me this
two days ago.

19:10.680 --> 19:12.822
You've got to get changed
for the Mrs. Claus sketch.

19:12.822 --> 19:14.724
I know.
In a second.

19:15.685 --> 19:17.857
You guys knew for
two days and didn't tell me?

19:18.928 --> 19:20.430
I only knew
for one day.

19:20.430 --> 19:22.432
We didn't want
to ruin your show.

19:22.432 --> 19:25.164
Oh, yeah? Well, how's that
working out for ya?

19:27.567 --> 19:28.868
Places!

19:28.868 --> 19:30.940
[bell rings]

19:32.502 --> 19:36.706
- Wow, you look great.
- Oh, yeah? How do my ears look?

19:36.706 --> 19:38.878
Good enough to nibble on?

19:39.379 --> 19:40.380
What?

19:41.881 --> 19:43.553
[Ronnie]
And... action!

19:44.614 --> 19:47.887
Ho, ho, ho!
Who's next?!

19:47.887 --> 19:51.661
Wait a minute,
you're not Santa.

19:52.892 --> 19:54.924
No, I'm Mrs. Claus.

19:54.924 --> 19:58.528
Santa's busy finishing up
all the toys for the
good girls and boys.

19:58.528 --> 20:02.432
And I'm here to make sure
all the bad kids...
[growling] get nothing.

20:03.273 --> 20:05.375
OK...

20:05.375 --> 20:08.508
So, have you been
a good little boy?

20:08.508 --> 20:10.240
[grunts]

20:10.240 --> 20:11.741
Yes, I have.

20:11.741 --> 20:13.883
[chuckles] No, you haven't.

20:13.883 --> 20:18.288
- [chuckles] Yes, I have.
All year long.
- Liar!

20:19.649 --> 20:24.394
Santa sees everything!
And so do I!

20:24.394 --> 20:26.256
We have little elves
that go to the clubs

20:26.256 --> 20:28.258
and take pictures
with their cell phones!

20:28.898 --> 20:30.430
What's going on?

20:32.562 --> 20:35.435
That miserable,
two-timing weasel!

20:35.435 --> 20:38.768
Oh! Mrs. Claus! I thought
I was getting a puppy!

20:38.768 --> 20:42.272
Oh, why? So you can
cheat on it with another puppy?

20:42.272 --> 20:43.673
In a tacky tube-top!

20:43.673 --> 20:45.815
[both grunting]

20:49.749 --> 20:53.323
- You want me to call "cut"?
- No, you can let this one go.

20:54.324 --> 20:55.825
[both grunting]

20:55.825 --> 20:57.527
I'm sorry.
I messed up!

20:57.527 --> 20:58.928
But it was only one puppy.

20:58.928 --> 21:01.260
There were lots of other puppies
that I never even looked at.

21:01.260 --> 21:05.635
Oh, well Santa does believe
in forgiveness.

21:05.635 --> 21:07.767
But Santa's not here!

21:07.767 --> 21:09.769
Eat snow, cheater!

21:09.769 --> 21:11.571
♪ Oh, yeah ♪♪

21:15.975 --> 21:18.408
So are the producers mad
I ruined the skit?

21:18.408 --> 21:20.680
Who cares. It was my
favorite part of the show.

21:22.682 --> 21:25.585
So I guess this means we're
on the naughty list, too?

21:25.585 --> 21:27.417
What do you think?

21:28.888 --> 21:30.520
When Jake did
what he did,

21:30.520 --> 21:32.422
he was thinking
about himself.

21:32.422 --> 21:34.794
When Lilly and Oliver
did what they did,

21:34.794 --> 21:36.596
they were thinking
about you.

21:38.598 --> 21:39.929
You have a
very wise dad.

21:41.601 --> 21:43.302
Suppose I do.

21:43.302 --> 21:44.934
So you forgive us?

21:44.934 --> 21:47.737
If I didn't, who else
would give me a hug right now?

21:51.411 --> 21:53.383
- Miley?
- Yo, yo, yo, yo, yo!

21:53.383 --> 21:55.645
Hey, guys, it's OK.

21:56.546 --> 21:58.448
- Listen, I...
- Jake.

21:59.419 --> 22:00.720
I know.

22:00.720 --> 22:04.724
You love me, you're sorry
and you want another chance.

22:04.724 --> 22:07.457
But I'm not gonna
get another one, am I?

22:10.800 --> 22:11.801
'Bye, Jake.

22:16.906 --> 22:20.510
If it makes you feel any better,
someone stole my clothes

22:20.510 --> 22:22.712
so I have to fly back
to Phoenix like this.

22:26.576 --> 22:28.718
OK, which one
of you all did it?

22:30.450 --> 22:31.851
That mean
I get a hug, too?
